Maven plugin for generating JNI headers
Last Published: 05 Jun 2013  | Version: 1.0.3
Overview
  • Introduction
  • Goals
  • Github project

jni-headers:javap

Full name:

com.alexkasko.maven:jni-headers-maven-plugin:1.0.3:javap

Description:

Runs javap on provided class and writes generated output formatted as C/C++ header file containing macros definitions for methods names and signatures

Attributes:

  • Requires a Maven project to be executed.

Required Parameters

Name Type Since Description
javapClass String - Class to run javap on
User property is: javapClass.
javapOutputFilePath File - Path to outputFile
User property is: javapOutputFile.

Optional Parameters

Name Type Since Description
javapParseErrorRegexString String - Regular expression to match javap error messages
Default value is: ^ERROR:.*$.
User property is: javapParseErrorRegex.
javapParseNameRegexString String - Regular expression to match javap method names
Default value is: ^.*\s+([^.\s]+)\(.*\);$.
User property is: javapParseNameRegex.
javapParseSignatureRegexString String - Regular expression to match javap method signatures
Default value is: ^\s+Signature:\s+(.+)$.
User property is: javapParseSignatureRegex.
javapPath File - Path to "javap" executable
User property is: javapPath.

Parameter Details

javapClass:

Class to run javap on
  • Type: java.lang.String
  • Required: Yes
  • User Property: javapClass

javapOutputFilePath:

Path to outputFile
  • Type: java.io.File
  • Required: Yes
  • User Property: javapOutputFile

javapParseErrorRegexString:

Regular expression to match javap error messages
  • Type: java.lang.String
  • Required: No
  • User Property: javapParseErrorRegex
  • Default: ^ERROR:.*$

javapParseNameRegexString:

Regular expression to match javap method names
  • Type: java.lang.String
  • Required: No
  • User Property: javapParseNameRegex
  • Default: ^.*\s+([^.\s]+)\(.*\);$

javapParseSignatureRegexString:

Regular expression to match javap method signatures
  • Type: java.lang.String
  • Required: No
  • User Property: javapParseSignatureRegex
  • Default: ^\s+Signature:\s+(.+)$

javapPath:

Path to "javap" executable
  • Type: java.io.File
  • Required: No
  • User Property: javapPath
